	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I say just write code and keep the screen left side turned off until all calculations are completed then set it to display. That'll give you a sense of how much more you can add to your game, because it'll visually show about what time your program completes.
<br />
<br />6502 assembly isn't hard IMO. I'm the opposite way though, I believe C is exponentially harder than assembly, unless your for some reason programming an intel chip.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


