		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, while reading code may be helpful, especially if is well-commented, but I learn more from tutorials where are not only code sample is presented but also there is explained why it is written so and not somehow else.
<br />
<br />Also you need to understand that I don't like c family of languages (maybe except c#), prefer simpler ones like pascal and basic, but here I don't have choice. Either C or ASM. Afaik there are no pascal/basic compilers with NES target (preferably pascal).

		

