	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The beautiful thing about CC65/KNES is that you can code in C and optimize bit by bit into separate CA65 assembly functions as needed. You get the readabilty of C with the optional speed of assembly. Just my layman's take on the matter.
<br />As others have said see the Alter Ego source for a great example of this.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


