	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The assembly routines in Alter Ego aren't game-specific, it is low-level stuff only, like setting up a sprite or playing music. All the game logic is written in C. So you can use them as a library and make a simple game without touching assembly much or at all.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


